content.location: Behind the big tree with Ranger Dangler on its left and Illusionary Mentor on its right.

content.description: Pulls the single big roof at the far left.
content.location: Left most route of main Huking Buttress wall with Beyond the Sea to its left and Giggle Stick to its right. (Some consider Beyond the Sea to be on Huking Buttress, others consider it part of Middle Earth. Beyond the Sea is the route on the arete that transitions from Middle Earth to the Huking Buttress wall its anchors are next to Huking Buttresses anchors.

content.description: Third from the left route that pulls both roofs.
content.location: Right of Big Huking Chicken and starts just left of the big tree.

content.location: Right of Master of Ceremonies and left of Giggle Sticks.

climbs.name: Big Hucking Chicken
climbs.fa: Luke Bowman, Sean O'Grady, Tommy Blackwell 2007

content.description: Route climbs up to a ledge protected by 2 bolts. There's a roof permadraw that is interesting to clip...if you don't clip this and you blow the clip, it may result in a scary fall, possibly a deck. The permadraw is long so it should be reachable by most...this route may be a bit more difficult for shorter people. Crux is pulling the roof onto face.
content.location: Left most route on insanity wall, however in an update to guidebook, this route is now considered to be located in the Beyond the Sea wall.

content.description: The crux is right at the permadraw. If you're a shorty... good luck pulling this move.
content.location: It's hard to find. I would recommend looking in the book for this one. The start is through some weird rock formation. It's a nice warm-up for the real climb.

content.description: Ledge with a low  and high roof between Middle Earth and Insanity. Gets shade most of the time.
